text:
The West End is one of London's most fashionable
and energetic neighborhoods,

and as its name implies, it's located just
west of old-town London.

Chic boutiques, cozy cafés and noisy pubs
are set in centuries-old buildings

that line the narrow streets, and everywhere
you go,
there are people out just having fun.

Historically the preserve of the rich and
well-to-do,

the West End once offered an escape from the
smog and crowds of industrial London.
Nowadays, it's open to everyone to enjoy,

and the trendy shops and eateries bring in
a youthful crowd.
The glowing billboards of Piccadilly Circus

are one of the most photographed sights in
London,

and nearby Trafalgar Square is a favorite
meeting spot,
with the National Gallery right next door.

The West End is also London's main theatrical
district,
and attracts stage shows from around the world.

The bars and restaurants along fashionable
Carnaby Street

hum with theatergoers and crowds enjoying
pre-show drinks.

From a once exclusive London getaway to a
bustling retail and entertainment quarter,

the West End is now one of the most popular
corners of London.
